he was right here.

191
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:57,858
If you don't mind,

192
00:12:57,942 --> 00:13:01,567
I'd appreciate it if you would
refrain from speaking his name.

193
00:13:01,650 --> 00:13:05,025
Hearing it aloud forces
me to think about him,

194
00:13:05,108 --> 00:13:08,233
and in turn, you receive
those memories, too.

195
00:13:08,317 --> 00:13:12,775
Receive those memories?
I'm not sure I...

196
00:13:12,858 --> 00:13:14,233
What's going on here?

197
00:13:14,317 --> 00:13:16,608
It's hard for me to explain.

198
00:13:16,692 --> 00:13:18,192
As long as I can remember,

199
00:13:18,275 --> 00:13:22,150
my inner thoughts have broadcast
themselves to those around me.

200
00:13:22,233 --> 00:13:25,983
Whether they're words, memories,
or whatever I imagine.

201
00:13:26,067 --> 00:13:28,650
Including your dreams.

202
00:13:28,733 --> 00:13:32,233
Wait just a minute.
How did I know that?

203
00:13:33,567 --> 00:13:36,650
[KIKI ASUKAI] There's someone
else here with us.

204
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:38,108
[whirring]

205
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:44,192
[FACE-LIFTER whistling]

206
00:13:49,108 --> 00:13:50,775
Who is that whistling?

207
00:13:50,858 --> 00:13:54,067
The person who's going
to kill me tonight.

208
00:13:54,150 --> 00:13:55,983
What do you mean?

209
00:13:59,317 --> 00:14:02,525
[FACE-LIFTER]
You there, Kiki?

210
00:14:03,733 --> 00:14:04,650
The hell?

211
00:14:04,733 --> 00:14:07,108
Man, what was that for?

212
00:14:07,192 --> 00:14:08,567
[NARIHISAGO]
Hitoshi Sonoda!

213
00:14:08,650 --> 00:14:11,150
Face-lifter? There's no way!

214
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:14,067
[FACE-LIFTER] Huh? How the
hell do you know my name?

215
00:14:14,150 --> 00:14:16,192
Because he's a police detective.

216
00:14:16,275 --> 00:14:17,983
A cop? That ain't right.

217
00:14:18,067 --> 00:14:19,942
If you can get inside
her dreams like me,

218
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:21,858
that means you're just
like the rest of us.

219
00:14:21,942 --> 00:14:23,525
Tonight's supposed
to be my turn!

220
00:14:23,608 --> 00:14:25,817
You'd better explain
yourself right now!

221
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:28,150
I'm the one who's
in the dark here!

222
00:14:30,608 --> 00:14:32,525
[NARIHISAGO]
He disappeared.

223
00:14:32,608 --> 00:14:36,233
He woke up because you
made him experience pain.

224
00:14:36,317 --> 00:14:37,567
It's different for me.

225
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:40,150
I always have to die before
I'm able to wake up.

226
00:14:40,233 --> 00:14:41,817
What do you mean?

227
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:43,150
What's with this id well?

228
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:45,775
Also, why do you
look like Kaeru?

229
00:14:45,858 --> 00:14:49,442
I told you, I have no idea
what you're talking about.

230
00:14:49,525 --> 00:14:51,108
Then tell me where I am.

231
00:14:51,192 --> 00:14:52,942
[KIKI ASUKAI]
I thought I was clear.

232
00:14:53,025 --> 00:14:57,233
You're asleep in your room,
and you entered my dream.

233
00:15:00,108 --> 00:15:02,275
Mom, look! Dad's awake!

234
00:15:02,358 --> 00:15:05,192
Don't scare us like
that ever again!

235
00:15:05,275 --> 00:15:06,525
Oh, thank goodness.

236
00:15:06,608 --> 00:15:08,483
We've been waiting for you
to regain consciousness

237
00:15:08,567 --> 00:15:09,525
since the incident.

238
00:15:09,608 --> 00:15:11,025
Since what?

239
00:15:11,108 --> 00:15:14,692
Don't you remember
stopping the Challenger?

240
00:15:14,775 --> 00:15:16,942
[AYAKO]
You were crying in your sleep.

241
00:15:17,025 --> 00:15:19,108
Was it a bad dream?

242
00:15:19,192 --> 00:15:20,150
A dream.

243
00:15:20,233 --> 00:15:22,608
[MUKU]
I'm so happy you're okay!

244
00:15:22,692 --> 00:15:25,150
Sorry if I had you
worried, kiddo.

245
00:15:25,233 --> 00:15:27,192
[MUKU]
I gotta ask.

246
00:15:27,275 --> 00:15:29,358
Was the reason you were
acting so weird that morning

247
00:15:29,442 --> 00:15:31,692
because of what happened?

248
00:15:31,775 --> 00:15:34,567
Did you go to the
Challenger ready to die?

249
00:15:34,650 --> 00:15:37,858
Of course not, Muku.
Don't be ridiculous.

250
00:15:37,942 --> 00:15:39,400
[MUKU]
You're right.

251
00:15:39,483 --> 00:15:42,817
Just don't die. Okay, Dad?

252
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:44,275
Are you kidding?

253
00:15:44,358 --> 00:15:47,525
You think I would die and
leave you two behind? Never.

254
00:15:47,608 --> 00:15:49,567
[MOMOKI] Narihisago,
there are several matters

255
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:53,067
we need to discuss,
but I suppose they can wait.

256
00:15:53,150 --> 00:15:54,567
In the meantime,

257
00:15:54,650 --> 00:15:57,275
looks like the incident will
be labeled as self-defense.

258
00:15:57,358 --> 00:16:01,233
Thank you, Momoki.
I'm still alive because of you.

259
00:16:06,442 --> 00:16:08,025
[KIKI ASUKAI]
Come in.

260
00:16:11,192 --> 00:16:16,150
It's Narihisago, isn't it?
First Investigative Division.

261
00:16:16,233 --> 00:16:18,317
You wanted to make
sure, didn't you?

262
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,733
It was real.

263
00:16:19,817 --> 00:16:22,900
A dream, yeah,
but that would mean...

264
00:16:22,983 --> 00:16:25,442
...you and I really
did share it.

265
00:16:26,733 --> 00:16:28,442
Making it a reality.

266
00:16:28,525 --> 00:16:30,983
At least, whatever the
definition of that word means

267
00:16:31,067 --> 00:16:33,108
in a place like this.

268
00:16:33,192 --> 00:16:35,483
If you'll allow me
a minute to explain,

269
00:16:35,567 --> 00:16:37,400
I want to share
my interpretation

270
00:16:37,483 --> 00:16:39,150
of what's going on.

271
00:16:39,233 --> 00:16:41,275
I noticed two things happening.

272
00:16:41,358 --> 00:16:44,525
First, like I said, we were
having the same dream.

273
00:16:44,608 --> 00:16:48,900
And second, I could read your
mind while it was happening.

274
00:16:48,983 --> 00:16:52,608
[KIKI ASUKAI] To be more
precise, you entered my dream,

275
00:16:52,692 --> 00:16:54,858
and you weren't reading my mind.

276
00:16:54,942 --> 00:16:58,983
More like it was
broadcasting itself to you.

277
00:16:59,067 --> 00:17:00,900
I can't explain why.

278
00:17:00,983 --> 00:17:02,317
The only thing I do know

279
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:06,108
is that I've never had
a secret all my own.

280
00:17:06,192 --> 00:17:08,733
[NARIHISAGO] There's one more
thing we haven't talked about.

281
00:17:08,817 --> 00:17:13,775
Why there was a serial killer
there with us out to murder you.

282
00:17:13,858 --> 00:17:16,567
They're the only kind
of people who appear.

283
00:17:16,650 --> 00:17:19,192
Like the man who wanted
to peel off my face.

284
00:17:19,275 --> 00:17:20,733
And you, as well.

285
00:17:20,817 --> 00:17:25,900
I'm not like him!
At least, not in this world.

286
00:17:25,983 --> 00:17:30,025
Miss Asukai, what is this world?

287
00:17:30,108 --> 00:17:32,233
I need to know what it is
I'm dealing with here

288
00:17:32,317 --> 00:17:34,108
if this is real.

289
00:17:34,192 --> 00:17:37,025
[KIKI ASUKAI]
Yes. It isn't a dream.

290
00:17:37,108 --> 00:17:39,942
I don't mean whether
it's imaginary,

291
00:17:40,025 --> 00:17:41,983
but then again,
someone from this world

292
00:17:42,067 --> 00:17:44,358
wouldn't know the difference.

293
00:17:44,442 --> 00:17:48,567
Sonoda said--the Face-lifter--
he mentioned something like,

294
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:52,025
"tonight was supposed
to be his turn"?

295
00:17:52,108 --> 00:17:53,483
What did he mean?

296
00:17:53,567 --> 00:17:55,650
He meant that particular dream.

297
00:17:55,733 --> 00:17:57,233
So if I understand
this correctly,

298
00:17:57,317 --> 00:17:59,442
you're saying other serial
killers appear to you

299
00:17:59,525 --> 00:18:00,608
on different nights?

300
00:18:00,692 --> 00:18:01,983
[KIKI ASUKAI]
Yes.

301
00:18:02,067 --> 00:18:04,400
If that's the truth, how can
you be so calm about it?

302
00:18:06,275 --> 00:18:07,900
Because for a long time now,

303
00:18:07,983 --> 00:18:11,400
these people have been coming
to murder me in my dreams.

304
00:18:11,483 --> 00:18:15,775
I get it. People like the
Challenger and his buddies.

305
00:18:15,858 --> 00:18:17,275
And when you fall asleep,

306
00:18:17,358 --> 00:18:20,317
the bastards slink outta
the shadows to murder you.

307
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,858
Over and over and over again.

308
00:18:22,942 --> 00:18:24,358
They have the perfect victim;

309
00:18:24,442 --> 00:18:26,483
one they can torture
endlessly in dreams.

310
00:18:26,567 --> 00:18:27,983
That's enough!

311
00:18:29,442 --> 00:18:31,400
Please stop it.

312
00:18:31,483 --> 00:18:33,358
Are you all right?

313
00:18:34,442 --> 00:18:35,400
Forgive me.

314
00:18:35,483 --> 00:18:36,900
I don't know why,

315
00:18:36,983 --> 00:18:39,650
but I can't seem to stop it
from broadcasting to you.

316
00:18:39,733 --> 00:18:41,858
All I see are flashes,

317
00:18:41,942 --> 00:18:44,900
but you... you keep
experiencing it in full

318
00:18:44,983 --> 00:18:47,400
with no way out except dying.

319
00:18:47,483 --> 00:18:50,150
[KIKI ASUKAI] At first,
there was only one killer.

320
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:54,067
But later on, he began calling
others into my dreams.

321
00:18:54,150 --> 00:18:55,650
[NARIHISAGO]
This man--

322
00:18:55,733 --> 00:18:59,317
he wouldn't happen to have
a top hat and cane.

323
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,650
[KIKI ASUKAI]
Yes.

324
00:19:02,025 --> 00:19:04,025
[NARIHISAGO]
Makes my stomach turn.

325
00:19:04,108 --> 00:19:05,067
[KIKI ASUKAI]
Real quick.

326
00:19:05,150 --> 00:19:06,400
Could you talk to the doctors

327
00:19:06,483 --> 00:19:09,525
and make them stop
giving me sedatives?

328
00:19:09,608 --> 00:19:11,525
Sleep's just part
of the problem.

329
00:19:11,608 --> 00:19:13,483
Not only do I see
myself being killed

330
00:19:13,567 --> 00:19:16,025
and reliving previous
deaths after I pass out,

331
00:19:16,108 --> 00:19:19,483
the medicines also make
it hard to concentrate.

332
00:19:19,567 --> 00:19:21,567
I'll see what I can do.

333
00:19:21,650 --> 00:19:24,400
Why do you think the Challenger
tried to kill you?

334
00:19:24,483 --> 00:19:26,108
In real life, I mean.

335
00:19:26,192 --> 00:19:28,608
He couldn't murder you
in dreams if he did.

336
00:19:28,692 --> 00:19:31,108
Dreams may be
similar to reality,

337
00:19:31,192 --> 00:19:33,608
but they're no substitute.

338
00:19:33,692 --> 00:19:36,983
That man wasn't only interested
in hurting other people.

339
00:19:37,067 --> 00:19:39,150
He enjoyed being hit himself.

340
00:19:39,233 --> 00:19:41,775
You don't get physically
injured in a dream.

341
00:19:41,858 --> 00:19:43,108
I think he kidnapped me

342
00:19:43,192 --> 00:19:45,983
because he needed to
actually feel that pain.

343
00:19:46,067 --> 00:19:47,442
Not anymore.

344
00:19:47,525 --> 00:19:49,942
Now that the
Challenger's is gone,

345
00:19:50,025 --> 00:19:52,442
does it ease your pain at all?

346
00:19:54,233 --> 00:19:57,108
[NARIHISAGO] I promise,
I'll find a way to end it.

347
00:20:00,108 --> 00:20:02,400
I hope so, Detective.

348
00:20:10,525 --> 00:20:11,650
Uh.

349
00:20:13,067 --> 00:20:16,275
[FACE-LIFTER] The cop? How the
hell'd you find this place?

350
00:20:16,358 --> 00:20:19,358
You told me about it
back when we met in prison.

351
00:20:19,442 --> 00:20:22,567
Prison? I ain't never
been to prison!

352
00:20:22,650 --> 00:20:25,775
'Cause I never had a reason to
be arrested in the first place!

353
00:20:25,858 --> 00:20:28,317
[NARIHISAGO] No, at least,
not at this stage.

354
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:30,650
Yeah! That's right!
I'm innocnt.

355
00:20:30,733 --> 00:20:32,358
All I did was mess
around in a dream

356
00:20:32,442 --> 00:20:34,525
and there's no law against that!

357
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:36,817
Wait, you said "at this stage."

358
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,067
There's no point worrying
yourself about it.

359
00:20:39,150 --> 00:20:40,858
Hey, who are you?

360
00:20:40,942 --> 00:20:43,817
You're one of us, right?
With you-know-who?

361
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:48,317
You mean, the guy with the cane?

362
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:52,233
No, and I'm not one of you.

363
00:20:52,317 --> 00:20:54,942
[FACE-LIFTER] You killed
the Challenger, didn't you?

364
00:20:55,025 --> 00:20:56,733
Here to kill me, too?

365
00:20:56,817 --> 00:21:01,442
[NARIHISAGO] I'm in no shape
for that. Just here to visit.

366
00:21:01,525 --> 00:21:03,733
You and I are going to
have a nice long talk.

367
00:21:03,817 --> 00:21:04,900
First, you're going to tell me

368
00:21:04,983 --> 00:21:06,608
what you know about
this Kiki girl,

369
00:21:06,692 --> 00:21:10,192
and the man who showed you
how to get inside her dreams.

370
00:21:10,275 --> 00:21:13,275
And afterwards,
we can focus on you.

371
00:21:13,358 --> 00:21:16,483
The reason why you like
to remove people's faces,

372
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:19,608
but you're too much of a
coward to rip off your own.

373
00:21:19,692 --> 00:21:23,733
Oh, we're gonna
have a lovely time.

374
00:21:34,733 --> 00:21:38,400
[inaudible]

375
00:21:39,942 --> 00:21:42,317
You don't have to die anymore!

376
00:21:44,900 --> 00:21:46,525
[AYAKO]
Morning.

377
00:21:46,608 --> 00:21:49,150
Sorry, I didn't mean
to startle you.

378
00:21:49,233 --> 00:21:53,192
[NARIHISAGO crying]

379
00:21:53,275 --> 00:21:55,900
[AYAKO]
Another bad dream, huh?

380
00:21:55,983 --> 00:21:58,567
So, who died?

381
00:21:58,650 --> 00:22:00,108
Was it me?

382
00:22:01,525 --> 00:22:04,775
I promise, I'm not gonna die,
you hear me?

383
00:22:04,858 --> 00:22:08,817
Never in a million years would
I leave you or Muku behind.

384
00:22:10,483 --> 00:22:11,650
Where is Muku?

385
00:22:11,733 --> 00:22:13,858
She was still tired from
the firework festival,

386
00:22:13,942 --> 00:22:16,358
but should be stopping by
sometime around noon.

387
00:22:16,442 --> 00:22:17,525
Ah.

388
00:22:17,608 --> 00:22:20,567
Are you sleeping well?
Tell me the truth.

389
00:22:20,650 --> 00:22:24,650
Me? I haven't slept well.
Not for a long time.

390
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:25,858
[AYAKO]
Since when?

391
00:22:25,942 --> 00:22:27,567
Oh, hard to say.

392
00:22:27,650 --> 00:22:29,692
Aki! You should've told me!

393
00:22:29,775 --> 00:22:32,442
Heh. I really wish
that I could have.

394
00:22:32,525 --> 00:22:36,358
I'm serious! Do you realize
how important sleep is?

395
00:22:36,442 --> 00:22:37,608
If you're not getting enough,

396
00:22:37,692 --> 00:22:40,317
it's like chipping away
years of your life.

397
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:41,567
Ah.

398
00:22:41,650 --> 00:22:43,108
[chuckles]

399
00:22:43,192 --> 00:22:45,817
In that case, I guess
it's only right

400
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:48,483
to try and help her get
a good night's rest.

401
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:50,067
Who do you mean?

402
00:22:50,150 --> 00:22:52,525
You're the one who
needs rest, Aki.

403
00:22:52,608 --> 00:22:55,317
I'm sorry I didn't
realize it sooner.

404
00:22:58,233 --> 00:23:01,442
[AYAKO]
What is it?

405
00:23:01,525 --> 00:23:05,817
Honey, I'm not sure why you're
afraid to close your eyes.

406
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:09,358
But if I die, you'll
know it's just a dream,

407
00:23:09,442 --> 00:23:12,233
and all you have
to do is wake up.

